name: Jeepers Anonymous
description: Hello!!! Do you own a jeep and want to join this amazing club that does everything from supporting our local community to off-roading?We do require $35 for dues, with that membership fee you receive decals and one club shirt!If you are over 16 and live in Oklahoma please email Karen our Secretary—jeepersanonymoussecretary@gmail.com
title: Jeepers Anonymous

name: Brad
The group does big and small wheeling events for all. You also have the life long friendships that Shelley and I have made. I see a group of people with huge hearts, big smiles, and making memories for a lifetime.
title: Brad

name: Cale and Sommer
Sommer and I came into this \"group\" not knowing anyone and didn't even know what to expect. We have since realized it's not a \"group\" it truly is a \"family\" that either one of us would do anything for.
title: Cale and Sommer

name: Chad
Jeepers anonymous has taught my family that Jeeping isn't only about building your rig and making it over every trail successfully. It's about making life long friendships and becoming so close to others that they are more like a big family rather than a jeep club.
title: Chad

name: Don
We soon found out that it was much more that just a \"club\" it was truly a family and also a public servant.
title: Don

name: Jeff
Seeing what this club stands for and has become truly blessed me and my family.
title: Jeff

name: Kelly
JA is a bit unusual in that a lot of people here give from the heart, and give of themselves. There are a lot of very talented people here who contribute that talent to the group. It's a very cool thing.
title: Kelly

name: Kelsey
I have never been a social person or liked meeting people, since I've joined JA I have found myself being more of a social person and every time I think doing something stupid I have that JA banner on my jeep and it helps me fly straight and I love every opportunity I get to invite and explain this group to anyone!
title: Kelsey

name: Michael
What I love is that we all will sacrifice something in our own life to be able to help someone else out in this jeep family. I want to say that I have found true friends within this club! And it itself has filled that void in my life that I have been missing! I love you all!!
title: Michael

name: Sharla
When we joined JA I was lost in my heart. Recently distanced from my Family to preserve my sanity. JA filled that hole in my heart. I learned that Family isn't always blood..it's those who love, support,encourage,share interests..people who make you want to be a better person.
title: Sharla

name: Tony
Haven't been here long but I can say even in the short time I've had this family has far exceeded my expectations.
title: Tony
